    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0f6c05a4_8708f2f6",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 473,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-09T19:00:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this can just use fPreviousBestNumFullyReceived, and then we can drop the method numFullyReceived. The reason onGetFrameInfo is const is that it\u0027s not expected to move forward in the stream. In the intended call sequence, onGetFrameCount will have updated fPreviousBestNumFullyReceived, and then this will just see the up to date value.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 473,
        "startChar": 61,
        "endLine": 473,
        "endChar": 85
      },
      "revId": "2a2531f8ce79159b971cbaf6e7c18e8acd00220c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3f0db57_835201d5",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 473,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-13T06:14:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "True, after onGetFrameCount was changed to actually update fNumFullyReceivedFrames. :-)\n\nI also moved the other place it gets updated from the seekFrame method to the decodeFoo methods, i.e. from where we possibly move backwards to where we move forwards, as that seemed cleaner conceptually.",
      "parentUuid": "0f6c05a4_8708f2f6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 473,
        "startChar": 61,
        "endLine": 473,
        "endChar": 85
      },
      "revId": "2a2531f8ce79159b971cbaf6e7c18e8acd00220c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4829d225_8e2d325a",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 473,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-15T20:54:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we need it in decodeFrame and decodeFrameConfig? I would have thought that the call in onGetFrameCount would ensure that it\u0027s up to date.",
      "parentUuid": "e3f0db57_835201d5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 473,
        "startChar": 61,
        "endLine": 473,
        "endChar": 85
      },
      "revId": "2a2531f8ce79159b971cbaf6e7c18e8acd00220c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b86d78d4_f0fbcf22",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 473,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-15T21:33:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we\u0027d *need* it if onGetFrameCount is guaranteed to be called beforehand. But it\u0027s cheap, and would let Chromium (or any other user of Skia) to skip the onGetFrameCount call when continuing a decode.",
      "parentUuid": "4829d225_8e2d325a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 473,
        "startChar": 61,
        "endLine": 473,
        "endChar": 85
      },
      "revId": "2a2531f8ce79159b971cbaf6e7c18e8acd00220c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "615d6439_770e9c18",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 473,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-17T11:27:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When you say continuing a decode, I think you mean attempting to decode the next frame, rather than continuing an incremental decode of an individual frame? The latter (which I was thinking initially) wouldn\u0027t seem to benefit from updating fNumFullyReceivedFrames, but I can see how the former would. Sgtm",
      "parentUuid": "b86d78d4_f0fbcf22",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 473,
        "startChar": 61,
        "endLine": 473,
        "endChar": 85
      },
      "revId": "2a2531f8ce79159b971cbaf6e7c18e8acd00220c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d58cd8cd_d08c7c21",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 615,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-09T19:00:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We don\u0027t actually do this, right? If we didn\u0027t have enough data, don\u0027t we reset the decoder?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 614,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 615,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "2a2531f8ce79159b971cbaf6e7c18e8acd00220c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d29e9ff6_3f9384ac",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 615,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-13T06:14:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We *do* actually do this. Consider 1 onStartIncrementalDecode call followed by multiple onIncrementalDecode calls. The 1 onStartIncrementalDecode will reset the decoder (via calling this-\u003eseekFrame), but none of the multiple onIncrementalDecode\u0027s will reset the decoder.",
      "parentUuid": "d58cd8cd_d08c7c21",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 614,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 615,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "2a2531f8ce79159b971cbaf6e7c18e8acd00220c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dedd193f_d2019654",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 615,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-15T20:54:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, I was getting ahead of myself. When Chromium needs to resume a decode, it calls onGetFrameCount prior to calling incrementalDecode. It seems reasonable that we could update Chromium to skip the call if we are continuing a decode.",
      "parentUuid": "d29e9ff6_3f9384ac",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 614,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 615,
        "endChar": 58
      },
